10-Monkey-Species Project -- Capstone project¶

1 .. Definition¶

Project Overview¶

The aim of the project is to find the best algorithm which will classify the 10-monkey-species with good accurecy¶

Recognizing the animal in the wild is critical for understanding the evolutionary process that guide bio diversity.

Iilegal trade is the most important concern which is causing the reducing number of species globally. So we need to do fight against such illegal trade and trafficking.

So there is urgent need to identify the species using some non-intrusive way. So using computer vision techniques this seems to be promising and easy to implement.

Since the humans are also evolved from monkeys the technique used for human facial identification may work. SO CNNs are going to help us to identify the type of monkey species.

Once the model has been developed people can use it as a part of mobile app which can be used to identify the image.

Not all Humans are capable of identifying all the types of monkeys. ML with CNN helps to identify the type of species You can find similar related work in this link https://arxiv.org/pdf/1804.08790.pdf

Problem Statement¶

Identifying the type of the moneky species from the given image. the type of the species we are classifying are

mantled_howler            
patas_monkey              
bald_uakari               
japanese_macaque          
pygmy_marmoset            
white_headed_capuchin     
silvery_marmoset          
common_squirrel_monkey    
black_headed_night_monkey 
nilgiri_langur

So here we are trying solve the multiclass classification problem

Steps involved are preprocess the data define a CNN model use softmax function to classify image using 10 probablities (10 classes) the one which has high probablity is the type of species

Metrics¶

Accuracy is important metric for the model in classifying the image. After model has been made how many test images the model correctly classified by number of test images

Accuracy = (total images correctly classified in test set )/(total images in test set)

Since the number of images are less. We will be using data augmentation. So this help in identifying the image in different locations in a frame

In Classification below metrics will help in understading if the model is good or not is

Classification Acuurecy : As difined above how many test images are getting classified correctly by model

Confusion Matrix : this matrix will give how many images are getting correctly classified and which are classified wrong.. false postives/false negitives

Log Loss / Cross entropy: works by penalizing false classificaton. useful for the multiclass classification problem. value near 0 is high accurecy .. near 1 is having low accurecy

For our model we will look at classification acucrecy and confusion matrix. we can use the algorithm which is having best score on acuurecy and confusion matrix

Dataset is downloaded from the https://www.kaggle.com/slothkong/10-monkey-species/¶

in this notebook we are going to work on the dataset of identifying the species type of monkey. we will be using CNN to identify the species type of monkey if the imput image is given

The plan to solve the issue¶

step 1: import all modules

step 2: import dataset (data augumentation )

step 3: create a simple CNN model to classify the image

step 4: FInding accurecy of CNN model created

step 5: use transfer learning

step 6: write a function using best algorithm

step 7: test and identify the algorithm

In classification technique when the data belonging to one class is very less compared to other class. With the imbalance in data the model can be more biased and inaccurate. The class which is having more data it will become overfit And less data class become underfit So to avoid this I will be using Imagegenator from keras which will take the traing dir (which contains sub dir per class)

Keras provides the ImageDataGenerator class that defines the configuration for image data preparation and augmentation. This includes capabilities such as:

Sample-wise standardization.
Feature-wise standardization.
ZCA whitening.
Random rotation, shifts, shear and flips.
Dimension reordering.
Save augmented images to disk.

Image genrator will return the sample of images when requested. we will use module with flow_from_dir which will take images from diffrent folder inside the given folder. each fodler represents one class used for training

Algorithms and Techniques¶

Simple CNN model¶

The CNN model are used for most of the computer vision probelem.

In MLP we use vector by flatting the matrix input for image.. But that needs more training and computatation power.

Instead we break the matrix in to very small matrix and give it to the next layer which we call local connected layer

For image recognisation connected layers make more sense than the simple neural net.

So we use small matrix (filter ) move over the image and create new matrix from it.

then we will use the activation function just like perceptrons which will activate the nodes having more relvenet info.

then we reduce the size of matrix in next layer by using pooling layers ..

Then we continue this process till next few layers and then we flatten the matrix to a vector and give it to fully connected layer..

Then we will use softmax function which will geive a probablity that this image belongs to this class

How CNN works

CNN uses filters which will look like small boxes (as specified by user 2x3 or 3x3 so on ) and move over the image and try to find patterns in the following way in diffrent layers

layer1 : first layer of our CNN clearly picks out very simple shapes and patterns like lines and blobs.

layer2 : second layer of the CNN captures complex ideas. circles , stripes , and rectangles

layer3 and so on : picks out complex combinations of features from the second layer things like grids, and honeycombs

The simple CNN model that i am going to use is

2 Conv layers

2 Max pooling layer

2 FC layer

Also i am going to use other deeplearning algorithms ResNet,inception which are famous on image detection

Inception¶

The Inception network was an important milestone in the development of CNN classifiers. Prior to its inception, most popular CNNs just stacked convolution layers deeper and deeper, hoping to get better performance.

Inception made the network wider than deeper.

What that means is using different size filters to caputre features this helps to caputre the same image with different sizes and image in different locations

This makes things more computational challenging. So they introduced 1x1 filters for dim reduction before 3x3 or 5x5

Resnet :¶

Resnet is one of the best algorithm for training deep neural networks..

One of the main issue we face while training deep network is vanishing gradients.. resnet sloves this issue by introducing the shotcuts (identity functions ) to its erlier layers Which means the gradients back propagates through the shortcut connections.

This helps to train the network which are deeper.

this also helps in reducing thr training erorors

from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, Activation, Dropout, Flatten, Dense
model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(32, (3, 3), input_shape=(150, 150, 3)))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
model.add(Conv2D(32, (3, 3)))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(512))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(num_classes))
model.add(Activation('softmax'))

confusion matrix data exploration¶

False positive: the model says it belongs to class A . but it belongs to some other class False Negitive: the model says it does not belong to class A. but actually it belongs to class A

so for example class D correct prediction and actuval correct : 19 predicted class D but belongs to class B: 2 False potive predicted class G but belongs to class D: 4 False negitive

Class C is looks good in prediction with nearly 90% success rate

3. Methodology¶

Data preprocessing:¶

Preprocessing is preparing the data for training

Randomizing the data :

Train/validation sets with labels

Normalize the data

All the above steps are done by the image genarator module of keras. So the data will be randomized
preprocess_input will normalize the data and make it ready for the module flow_from_directory will create the dataset and labelset needed for training and validation

Implementation:¶

the implementation of the algorithm has 2 stages

Training the classifier 
Creating the module which will detect the type of specifies if image is given

During the first stage, the classifier was trained on the preprocessed training data. This was done in a Jupyter notebook and can be further divided into the following steps:

  1. Load both the training and validation images into memory
  2. Define the CNN network architectures 
       How many  conv layers / pool layers / FC layers
  3. defining the loss/ accuracy function
  4. monitor the training /validation errors during the epochs
  5. if accuracy less tune parameters and retrain
  6. once accuracy is reached we are done

In second stage we will build the function which we will use the train model to detect the future images

    x = image.img_to_array(img)
    x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)
    return  preprocess_input(x)
challenges faced¶

Data Imbalance:

One of the biggest issue that we need to deal with classification probelm is data imbalance . If number of images in one class is more than other class this creates overfitting/underfittin of that respective  class. We need to deal with data imbalance with data augmenation technique

Finding best gradient algorithm:

we have so many gradeint decent techniques that needs to be  checked and find the one which gives best results. The gradient algorithm supports below optimization techniques 

Momentum
Nestrov accelarated grdient
Adagrad 
Adadelta
RMSprop
Adam
Adamax 
Nadam
Amsgrad

Choosing the best one for your model is tough task.  most of the time you end up with trail and error method.  The one i have choosen if ADAM Adaptive Moment Estimation (Adam) .. this technique uses adaptive learning rate for each paramter.  In addition to storing an exponentially decaying average of past squared gradients  like Adadelta and RMSprop, Adam also keeps an exponentially decaying average of past gradients.  Adam behaves like a heavy ball with friction, which thus prefers flat minima in the error surface.
more info can be found from 
http://ruder.io/optimizing-gradient-descent/

Finding best algoritms in deep learning:

 We have so many deep learning techniques starting with  

    Alexnet 
    VGG 
    Resnet 
    Inception 
    Xception 


 Now choosing best algorithm  from them is going to be trail and error method.. each algorithm will have its own advantages and disadvantages.. 
 When you select models like vgg19 , resnet, incpetion and xception  they are deep and needs a lot computation for training .. 

 The Inception network was an important milestone in the development of CNN classifiers. Prior to its inception (punintended), most popular CNNs just stacked convolution layers deeper and deeper, hoping to get better performance.

 Inception made the network wider than deeper. 
 What that means is using different size filters to caputre   features this helps to caputre the  same image with different sizes  and image in different locations. This makes things more computational challenging. So  they introduced 1x1 filters for dim reduction before 3x3 or 5x5. This is useful for our model beacuse the monkey images are not properly placed. they are moved around the frame.  

 Restnet : they are fast to train becasue of residual nets(shortcuts). this helps backpropagation of error fast.. 

 Xception : is going to be one of the other algorithm to try. beacuse it takes each input layer separatly..  that means diffrent fillters for diffrent channels of inputs.. this helps  good for color images  and images of diffrent color species.

Importnant points to be remembered for coding

    Dataaugementation : via Image generator 
    Transfer learning : when you start the model training try to intilize weiights  with imagenet data. this makes traing fast 
    Confusion Matrix:    you can use normal  scikit learn confuion matrix. But  the pretty print confusion matrix looks nice  and giving more details of data
Transfer Learning¶

Transfer learning involves taking a pre-trained neural network and adapting the neural network to a new, different data set.

We will be using imagenet weights

We will try to use inception and resenet32 models and try to find which will give best accurecy for us.. depending on the results we will use the one for our model
